  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Thoracoscopic ablation is a promising treatment of persistent atrial fibrillation. However,&#xD;
      the postoperative rehabilitation is very important to prevent early recurrence of atrial&#xD;
      arrhythmia. The purpose of this study is to evaluate the efficacy of professional cardiac&#xD;
      rehabilitation in patients after thoracoscopic ablation.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
